section.t:
This document is organized as follows: 
         
            provides the terminology; 
         
         
            provides an overview
           of the SPPP protocol, including the layering approach,
           functional entities and data model;  
            specifies requirements for
           SPPP transport protocols;  
            describes the base protocol data structures including the request and response elements (), the response codes and messages () and the basic object type most first class objects extend from;
            
             and  describe the main protocol commands and examples;
           
         
            defines XML
           considerations that XML parsers must meet to conform to
           this specification;  
           normatively defines the SPPP protocol using its XML Schema Definition.
